From: Service Sam Electric schema cleanup
Subject: [PATCH] Fix JSON-LD schema bugs (image URL, aggregateRating, sameAs, geo)

The existing schema has three issues that can trip Google's structured-data
validator and one that risks a manual action for inflated review counts:

1. `image` is a base64 data: URI — Google's parser requires a URL.
2. `aggregateRating.reviewCount: 10` doesn't match the 3 reviews visible on
    the page, and inflating counts is against Google's structured-data
    policy (can trigger a manual action that removes rich results sitewide).
3. No `sameAs` — Google uses this for entity resolution between the site,
    the Google Business Profile, and third-party review platforms.
4. No `geo` coordinates — helpful for local search ranking.
5. No `@id` anchor — needed so Service schema on sub-pages can reference
    this business as their `provider`.

This patch also adds `hasOfferCatalog` listing all services so that sub-pages
can be discovered through the main entity.

Before merging: set `reviewCount` below to the REAL current count from the
Google Business Profile (must be <= reviews available on page or linked GBP;
when in doubt, set to the on-page count of 3).
---
 index.html | 77 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 75 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

